reviews.text: The work they are doing is amazing. The preservation of Mayan textiles is key for Guatemalan identity and deep rooted into the culture. The people that work there are very nice, very devoted to what they do.
Second trip, saw all three movies.....another must see if you have never been! Dont forget to hit up the gift shop, traditional items available but also really fun and artistic items!

Definitely worth the trip. Make sure you hit all the parts of it, like the downstairs part connected to the mall. Climbing the mound in the courtyard gives an idea of what it was like to summit a Mayan temple--they were talking.

Great meat, excellent service. They even got a shuttle to drive you to your hotel! Well done!
Best steaks and entrees I’ve had in the area. Use their shuttle service from any of the local hotels. Excellent service. Avocado salad is enormous.
Great place and great service the food is quite expensive but it worth it. Very good parking spaces and free ice cream. The barbecue is marvelous.
Wonderful meat. It is a must when visiting Guatemala City. Must try the Torti Carne (tortillas bathed in meats liquids and then cooked in the fire) they are crispy and perfect.

We ate here tonight & really loved the patio area. The atmosphere would have been phenomenal except that they were playing a weird mix of oldies. We felt some spanish guitar music would have fit much better. We shared a one person lomito & shrimp plate & added sides. It was plenty of food & delicious! We ordered the lava cake (based on a positive review we read) & the cheesecake to go. They were both horrible. I didn’t know you could mess up such simple desserts but they were not even edible. The cheesecake tasted several days old & the lava cake didn’t even have “lava” it was just a dry lump of burnt flour flavored slighty like chocolate. There is definite room for improvement but we would go again for the meal.

Every time I go to Guatemala City for a surgical mission trip, I come here.  There is a variety of food for everyone’s palate and it never disappoints.  This year, we asked the mariachi to play their favorite song.  The staff is friendly and the service prompt.

Visited Los Cebollines restaurant with a large group.  They seated us quickly, provided great service and the food was tasty.  The "meter of meat" was a serving to behold and all other food presentation was elegant.  The chicken fajitas were well seasoned.  The restaurant atmosphere, ambiance and decoration were well thought out and beautiful.
